<div style="text-align:center"><div style="width:8.5in;text-align:left;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto">
 <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold">Item&#8201;2.02 Results of Operations and Financial Condition. </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On January&#160;13, 2025, ARS Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) announced certain of its preliminary unaudited financial results for the three months ended December&#160;31, 2024 in the press release attached hereto as Exhibit 99.1, which is incorporated herein by reference. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The information in this Item 2.02 of this Current Report on&#160;Form <span style="white-space:nowrap">8-K,</span> including Exhibit 99.1,&#160;is furnished and shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for purposes of Section&#160;18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;), or otherwise subject to the liabilities of that Section, nor shall it be deemed incorporated by reference into any filing under the Exchange Act or the Securities Act of 1933, as amended (the &#8220;Securities Act&#8221;), whether made before or after today&#8217;s date, regardless of any general incorporation language in such filing. </p> <p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold">Item&#8201;7.01 Regulation FD Disclosure. </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On January&#160;13, 2025, the Company updated its corporate presentation for use with investors, analysts and others at the 43<sup style="font-size:75%; vertical-align:top">rd</sup> Annual J.P. Morgan Healthcare Conference. A copy of the presentation is attached as Exhibit 99.2 to this Current Report on <span style="white-space:nowrap">Form&#160;8-K.</span> </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The information in this Item 7.01 of this Current Report on <span style="white-space:nowrap">8-K,</span> including Exhibit 99.2, is furnished and shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for purposes of Section&#160;18 of the Exchange Act, or otherwise subject to the liabilities of that Section, nor shall it be deemed incorporated by reference into any filing under the Exchange Act or the Securities Act, whether made before or after today&#8217;s date, regardless of any general incorporation language in such filing. </p> <p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold">Item&#8201;9.01 Financial Statements and Exhibits </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">(d)</p> <p style="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>EX-99.1</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE" STYLE="line-height:Normal">

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="right"><B>Exhibit 99.1 </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g910559snap1.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>ARS Pharmaceuticals Announces Preliminary Fourth Quarter 2024 Financial </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Results and 2025 Objectives for </B><B><I>neffy</I></B><B></B><B><I><SUP STYLE="font-size:75%; vertical-align:top">&reg;</SUP></I></B><B>
(epinephrine nasal spray) </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><I>Preliminary fourth quarter
</I><B><I>neffy</I></B><I><SUP STYLE="font-size:75%; vertical-align:top">&reg;</SUP> net product revenue of approximately $6.5&nbsp;million </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><I>Preliminary cash, cash equivalents and short-term investments of $314.0&nbsp;million at <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">year-end</FONT> 2024
to support an operating runway of at least three years </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><I>Company to present at
43<SUP STYLE="font-size:75%; vertical-align:top">rd</SUP> Annual J.P. Morgan Healthcare Conference on Wednesday, January&nbsp;15, 2025 at 7:30am PT </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>SAN DIEGO, January</B><B></B><B>&nbsp;13, 2025</B> &#150; ARS Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (Nasdaq: SPRY), a biopharmaceutical company dedicated to empowering <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">at-risk</FONT> patients and caregivers to better protect themselves from allergic reactions that could lead to anaphylaxis, today announced preliminary, unaudited <B><I>neffy</I></B><SUP
STYLE="font-size:75%; vertical-align:top">&reg;</SUP> (epinephrine nasal spray) net product revenue for the fourth quarter and full year 2024 and outlined its 2025 commercial and clinical objectives. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;For ARS Pharma, 2024 marked a pivotal year, securing regulatory approvals for <B><I>neffy</I></B> as the first and only intranasal epinephrine
treatment, laying a solid foundation for our commercial success in the United States and expansion worldwide through partnerships. While early in the launch of <B><I>neffy</I></B>, the first three months of sales have exceeded expectations with very
positive demand indicators,&#148; said Richard Lowenthal, President and CEO of ARS Pharma. &#147;Looking ahead to 2025, we are poised to accelerate the growth of <B><I>neffy</I></B> through targeted commercial initiatives, including advancing
education and awareness among our key prescribers, achieving over 80&nbsp;percent commercial insurance coverage and launching impactful <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">direct-to-consumer</FONT></FONT> marketing
campaigns for the <B><I>neffy</I></B> brand. <B><I>neffy</I></B> is transforming the lives of patients by offering a simple, effective, and life-saving treatment option, and we are very pleased to be making such a meaningful difference in the lives
of patients, families and caregivers.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Preliminary Fourth Quarter 2024 Financial Results </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt"><B>Product revenue:</B> Preliminary <B><I>neffy</I></B> net product revenue for the fourth quarter of 2024 was
approximately $6.5&nbsp;million, with total net product sales for 2024 of approximately $7.1&nbsp;million since <B><I>neffy</I></B> became available to wholesalers and pharmacies on September&nbsp;23, 2024. More than 14,500 <B><I>neffy</I></B> <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">two-pack</FONT> units were delivered in the fourth quarter of 2024, including more than 1,500 units in the last week of 2024. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt"><B>Cash position:</B> Cash, cash equivalents and short-term investments were approximately $314.0&nbsp;million as
of December&nbsp;31, 2024. ARS Pharma reiterates its guidance that the company expects its cash, cash equivalents and short-term investments to be sufficient to fund its current operating plan for at least three years. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>2025 Key Strategic Priorities for Accelerating </B><B><I>neffy</I></B><B> U.S. Sales and Recent Highlights </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt"><B>Increase demand and traction among target prescribers</B>, with continued sales force and medical science
liaison engagement, expansion of the company&#146;s <B><I>neffy</I></B> Experience Program, and rollout of additional continuing medical education (CME) programs </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">More than 3,000 healthcare providers have prescribed <B><I>neffy</I></B> to date, of which 80&nbsp;percent are in
the highest decile categories for prescribing epinephrine </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">More than 1,750 healthcare providers have participated in the <B><I>neffy</I></B> Experience Program
</P></TD></TR></TABLE>
</DIV></Center>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g910559snap1.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">Express Scripts, the second largest pharmacy benefits manager in the U.S., added <B><I>neffy</I></B> to its
commercial national formularies in November 2024 </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

80&nbsp;percent commercial coverage by the end of the third quarter of 2025 </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-to-net</FONT></FONT> revenue of 50&nbsp;percent </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#145;back-to-school&#146;</FONT></FONT> season, the campaign will extend throughout the summer, driving brand recognition and encouraging patients to request <B><I>neffy</I></B> by
name </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Education (FARE) is set to launch a public service announcement campaign featuring a celebrity ambassador with ARS support later this year </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt"><B>Obtain approval of </B><B><I>neffy </I></B><B>1 mg for children</B> who weigh 15 to 30 kg
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">The sNDA filed with the U.S. FDA for <B><I>neffy</I></B> for children who weigh 15 to 30 kg has a Prescription
Drug User Fee Act (PDUFA) target action date of March&nbsp;6, 2025 </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">Based on review timelines and subject to approval, product availability of <B><I>neffy</I></B><B> 1 mg</B> is
expected in the second quarter of 2025 </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Presentation at the 43<SUP STYLE="font-size:75%; vertical-align:top">rd</SUP> Annual J.P.
Morgan Healthcare Conference </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On Wednesday, January&nbsp;15, 2025, at 7:30am PT, Richard Lowenthal, President and CEO of ARS Pharma, will present a
company overview at the 43<SUP STYLE="font-size:75%; vertical-align:top">rd</SUP> Annual J.P. Morgan Healthcare Conference. A live webcast of the presentation and Q&amp;A session can be accessed <U>here</U> or by visiting the investors section of
the company&#146;s website at <U><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">www.ir.ars-pharma.com</FONT></U>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>About Preliminary Financial Results </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The preliminary results set forth above are unaudited, are based on management&#146;s initial review of the company&#146;s results for the quarter ended
December&nbsp;31, 2024, and are subject to revision based upon the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">company&#146;s&nbsp;year-end&nbsp;closing</FONT> procedures and the completion and external audit of the
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">company&#146;s&nbsp;year-end&nbsp;financial</FONT> statements. Actual results may differ materially from these preliminary unaudited results following the completion
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">of&nbsp;year-end&nbsp;closing</FONT> procedures, final adjustments or other developments arising between now and the time that the company&#146;s financial results are finalized. In addition, these preliminary
unaudited results are not a comprehensive statement of the company&#146;s financial results for the quarter and year ended December&nbsp;31, 2024, should not be viewed as a substitute for full, audited financial statements prepared in accordance
with generally accepted accounting principles, and are not necessarily indicative of the company&#146;s results for any future period. </P>
</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always"> </p>
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g910559snap1.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>About
</B><B><I>neffy</I></B><B></B><B><I><SUP STYLE="font-size:75%; vertical-align:top">&reg;</SUP></I></B><B> </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>neffy </I></B>is an intranasal
epinephrine product for patients with Type I allergic reactions due to insect stings or bites, foods, medicinal products, other allergens, as well as idiopathic or exercise induced anaphylaxis that could lead to life-threatening anaphylaxis. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">INDICATION AND IMPORTANT SAFETY INFORMATION FOR <B><I>neffy </I></B>(epinephrine nasal spray) </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">INDICATION </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>neffy </I></B>2 mg is indicated for emergency
treatment of Type I allergic reactions, including anaphylaxis, in adult and pediatric patients who weigh 30 kg or greater. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">IMPORTANT SAFETY INFORMATION
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">It is recommended that patients are prescribed and have immediate access to two <B><I>neffy</I></B> nasal sprays at all times. In the absence of clinical
improvement or if symptoms worsen after initial treatment, administer a second dose of <B><I>neffy</I></B> in the same nostril with a new nasal spray starting 5 minutes after the first dose. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>neffy </I></B>is for use in the nose only. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Advise
patients when to seek emergency medical assistance for close monitoring of the anaphylactic episode and in the event further treatment is required. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Absorption of <B><I>neffy</I></B> may be affected by underlying structural or anatomical nasal conditions. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Administer with caution to patients who have heart disease; epinephrine may aggravate angina pectoris or produce ventricular arrhythmias. Arrhythmias,
including fatal ventricular fibrillation, have been reported, particularly in patients with underlying cardiac disease or taking cardiac glycosides, diuretics, or anti-arrhythmics. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The presence of a sulfite in <B><I>neffy </I></B>should not deter use. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><I>neffy</I></B> may alter nasal mucosa for up to 2 weeks after administration and increase systemic absorption of nasal products, including
<B><I>neffy</I></B>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Patients with certain medical conditions or who take certain medications for allergies, depression, thyroid disorders, diabetes, and
hypertension, may be at greater risk for adverse reactions. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Epinephrine can temporarily exacerbate the underlying condition or increase symptoms in
patients with the following: hyperthyroidism, Parkinson&#146;s disease, diabetes, renal impairment. Epinephrine should be administered with caution in patients with these conditions, including elderly patients and pregnant women. </P>
</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always"> </p>
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g910559snap1.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Adverse reactions to <B><I>neffy</I></B> may include throat irritation, intranasal paresthesia, headache,
nasal discomfort, feeling jittery, paresthesia, fatigue, tremor, rhinorrhea, nasal pruritus, sneezing, abdominal pain, gingival pain, hypoesthesia oral, nasal congestion, dizziness, nausea, and vomiting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">These are not all of the possible side effects of <B><I>neffy</I></B>. To report suspected adverse reactions, contact ARS Pharmaceuticals Operations, Inc. at <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">1-877-MY-NEFFY</FONT></FONT></FONT> <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(877-696-3339)</FONT></FONT> or FDA at <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">1-800-FDA-1088</FONT></FONT></FONT> or www.fda.gov/medwatch. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">For additional information on <B><I>neffy</I></B>, please see Full Prescribing Information at www.<B><I>neffy</I></B>.com. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>About Type I Allergic Reactions Including Anaphylaxis </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Type I allergic reactions are serious and potentially life-threatening events that can occur within minutes of exposure to an allergen and require immediate
treatment with epinephrine, the only <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">FDA-approved</FONT> medication for these reactions. While epinephrine autoinjectors have been shown to be highly effective, there are well published limitations that result in
many patients and caregivers delaying or not administering treatment in an emergency situation. These limitations include fear of the needle, lack of portability, needle-related safety concerns, lack of reliability, and complexity of the devices.
There are approximately 40&nbsp;million people in the United States who experience Type I allergic reactions. Of this group, over the last three years, approximately 20&nbsp;million people have been diagnosed and treated for severe Type I allergic
reactions that may lead to anaphylaxis, but (in 2023, for example) only 3.2&nbsp;million filled their active epinephrine autoinjector prescription, and of those, only half consistently carry their prescribed autoinjector. Even if patients or
caregivers carry an autoinjector, more than half either delay or do not administer the device when needed in an emergency. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>About ARS Pharmaceuticals,
Inc. </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">ARS Pharmaceuticals is a biopharmaceutical company dedicated to empowering <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">at-risk</FONT> patients and their
caregivers to better protect patients from allergic reactions that could lead to anaphylaxis. The company is commercializing<B><I>&nbsp;neffy</I></B><B><I><SUP STYLE="font-size:75%; vertical-align:top">&reg;</SUP></I></B>&nbsp;2 mg (trade
name<B>&nbsp;EUR</B><B><I>neffy</I></B><B><I><SUP STYLE="font-size:75%; vertical-align:top">&reg;</SUP></I></B>&nbsp;in the EU) (previously referred to as <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">ARS-1),</FONT> an epinephrine nasal spray indicated in the
U.S. for emergency treatment of Type I allergic reactions, including anaphylaxis, in adult and pediatric patients who weigh 30 kg or greater, and in the EU for emergency treatment of allergic reactions (anaphylaxis) due to insect stings or bites,
foods, medicinal products, other allergens, as well as idiopathic or exercise induced anaphylaxis in adults and children who weigh 30 kg or greater. For more information, visit&nbsp;<U><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">www.ars-pharma.com</FONT></U>.
</P>
</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always"> </p>

Allergic Reactions neffy&#174;: first and only FDA and EC approved &#8220;no needle, no injection&#8221; solution for Type I allergic reactions Strong execution during first 3 months of launch in Q4 2024 sets foundation for delivering significant
neffy US sales in 2025 Prescribing breadth: ~50% of high decile HCPs targeted to date have prescribed neffy Secured coverage with payers at ~50% total gross to net, and &gt;80% commercial coverage anticipated by end of Q3 2025 Potential
multi-billion US market opportunity ($3 billion Rx&#8217;ed segment, and up to $7 billion expansion segment) driven by HCP and consumer preference and adoption1 NCE-like IP exclusivity potential&#160;with issued composition of matter and method of

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always"> </p>
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER"> <p style="margin-bottom:0pt" align="center">
<img src="g910559ex99_2s4g1.jpg" alt="Slide 4" title="Slide 4" ></p> <p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:1pt;line-height:0pt;color:#FFFFFF;"><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:1pt;"> Type I Allergy Patients Face
Significant Limitations with Other Treatment Options that neffy may help to address References: 1. Warren CM, et al. Ann Allergy Asthma Immunol. 2018. 2. Rooney E, et al. Poster Presentation at ACAAI 2022 (Louisville, KY). 3. Brooks C, et al. Ann
Allergy Asthma Immunol. 2017. 4. El Turki A, et al. Emerg Med J. 2017. 5. Asthma and Allergy Foundation of American Patient Survey Report 2019. 6. Mehta GD, et al. Expert Rev Clin Immunol. 2023. 7. ARS company estimates based on IQVIA data and
references 1 through 6. Rapid administration without a needle No risk of needle-related injuries; lacerations2 or cardiotoxic blood vessel injections Less hesitation to dose NO NEEDLE NO INJECTION Fits in your pocket; easy to carry the recommended 2
devices ~10% of cases require repeat doses of epinephrine1 EASIER AND MORE CONSISTENT DOSING Simple place and press administration (no hold time) 100% of adults and children dosed neffy successfully in human factors studies by reading the commercial
instructions for use (IFU) RELIABLE 99.999% delivery of effective dose in reliability testing; not obstructed by any anaphylaxis symptoms; no inhalation required 30-month shelf-life at room temperature, with neffy stored at up to 3 months at high
temperatures (122oF) Only 50% carry one1 (&lt;20% carry two) ~25% - 60% do not administer, 1,3 5, 6 NO TREATMENT READILY AVAILABLE REFUSAL OF TREATMENT ~40% - 60% of patients delay2 DELAY IN TREATMENT 23% - 35% fail to dose correctly4 USER ERROR IN

// Edgar(tm) Renderer was created by staff of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  Data and content created by government employees within the scope of their employment are not subject to domestic copyright protection. 17 U.S.C. 105.
var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}

/* Updated 2009-11-04 */
/* v2.2.0.24 */

/* DefRef Styles */

	font-size: 1em;

}

	display: block;
	font-weight: bold;
}

	margin-top: 0px;

	background-color: #2F4497;

	color: black;

}
